The paper discusses new stable merge sort algorithms and provides upper and lower bounds for several merge sort algorithms, which are topics typically studied in computer science sub-categories such as data structures (cs.DS), algorithms (cs.AL), computational complexity (cs.CC), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and game theory (cs.GT). However, since the focus is on sorting algorithms, cs.DS and cs.AL are the most likely sub-categories.
